content.description: This covers all of the current "routes" in this area.  All follow crimpy lake stones with not much variation.  A dihedral route is possible, as is mantling on a small ledge and pulling some sick roof moves in the tunnel.  All are pretty fun...all can be slimey...but nonetheless, get out there and get on it...someone put a lot of work into this!

Hardly worth note, this is a grouping of rocks glued to the concrete bridge where Chester Creek flows into Lake Superior.  Not sure who actually did the work, but it's a fun little diversion and do-able by headlamp. 

  Room for about 4 ropes and all the routes follow crimpy little lake stones glued to the face.
